# LunarFlux AI — Cursor Rules

## Framework & Environment
- Always use **Next.js 16 App Router** (`app/` directory) — NOT Pages Router
- Project is configured with `output: 'export'` (static export) — no server-side runtime
- React version follows Next.js built-in canary (React 19 compatible)

## Styling
- Prefer **inline `style` props** or **CSS Modules** for component styling (current project convention)
- For hover/focus effects in Server Components, use `<style>` tag with CSS class selectors — NOT JS event handlers
- Do NOT introduce Tailwind CSS unless the user explicitly requests a migration

## Server vs Client Components
- Default to **Server Components** (no `'use client'` at top)
- Add `'use client'` ONLY when using: `useState`, `useEffect`, `useRef`, browser APIs, or event handlers
- **NEVER** put `export const metadata` and `'use client'` in the same file — split into separate files

```tsx
// ❌ WRONG
'use client'
export const metadata = { title: '...' }

// ✅ CORRECT — split into two files
// page.tsx  →  export const metadata  (Server Component)
// ui.tsx    →  'use client'           (Client Component)
```

## Static Export Constraints
- Dynamic routes must define `generateStaticParams()`
- `useSearchParams()` must be wrapped in `<Suspense>`
- No Route Handlers or Middleware (not supported in static export)
- Use plain `<img>` or external image CDN instead of `next/image` optimizer

## Routing & Navigation
- Page links: `<Link href="...">` from `next/link`
- Programmatic navigation: `useRouter()` from `next/navigation`
- External links: plain `<a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">`

## SEO & Metadata
```tsx
import type { Metadata } from 'next'
export const metadata: Metadata = {
  title: '페이지 제목 | LunarFlux AI',
  description: '페이지 설명',
  keywords: ['키워드1', '키워드2'],
  openGraph: { title: '...', description: '...', images: ['/og.png'] },
}
```

## Git & Deployment
- Always `git add` → `git commit` → `git push origin main` after completing tasks
- Commit messages in English, imperative style: `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`, `docs:`
- Deployment via Vercel (auto-deploys on push to main)

## Reference
- Next.js official docs: https://nextjs.org/docs
- App Router guide: https://nextjs.org/docs/app
- Static exports: https://nextjs.org/docs/app/guides/static-exports
